The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also introduces new constraints on curvature, which are relevant to optimization problems in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications of string submodular functions in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
